1
00:00:01,701 --> 00:00:04,104
[Deib] Your ex seemed to enjoy
dancing with you!

2
00:00:04,237 --> 00:00:05,270
Did you guys kiss?

3
00:00:05,405 --> 00:00:06,639
I deserve the truth, Max.

4
00:00:06,772 --> 00:00:08,073
And I deserve your trust!

5
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:09,175
If that's what you think,

6
00:00:09,308 --> 00:00:10,577
then you never
trusted me at all!

7
00:00:10,710 --> 00:00:13,545
We found the private
investigator that Deib hired.

8
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:16,716
We also found out
that he's in this hospital.

9
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:17,783
[Evita] This is my patient!

10
00:00:17,917 --> 00:00:20,286
-What room?
-What are we standing here for?

11
00:00:20,652 --> 00:00:21,888
[Evita]
He died of cardiac arrest.

12
00:00:23,088 --> 00:00:25,524
[monitor flatlining]

13
00:00:25,992 --> 00:00:27,594
Max, I was part of the gang

14
00:00:27,727 --> 00:00:29,396
that attempted to carnap
Deib and Dale's car.

15
00:00:36,936 --> 00:00:38,237
Max, I was part of the gang

16
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:40,439
that attempted to carnap
Deib and Dale's car.

17
00:00:41,341 --> 00:00:42,442
[Bhaves] What?!

18
00:00:49,082 --> 00:00:50,817
[stutters] What?

19
00:00:53,051 --> 00:00:54,253
Max, I'm sorry.

20
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:57,856
[Bhaves]
Why did you need to carnap?

21
00:00:59,225 --> 00:01:01,226
Mom, do you remember when...

22
00:01:02,128 --> 00:01:03,595
Max had dengue?

23
00:01:04,664 --> 00:01:07,634
We didn't have money
to pay the hospital.

24
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,469
The doctor said...

25
00:01:11,438 --> 00:01:13,972
he wouldn't help Max

26
00:01:15,108 --> 00:01:19,646
until we paid the 75,000
we already owed the hospital.

27
00:01:21,346 --> 00:01:23,415
[Boyet sniffles]
I tried getting a loan,

28
00:01:23,549 --> 00:01:25,617
but nobody wanted
to lend me money.

29
00:01:26,152 --> 00:01:30,689
That's why I went
to my friend Tiago.

30
00:01:31,790 --> 00:01:34,760
He said he knew
a good side hustle.

31
00:01:35,795 --> 00:01:40,700
I'd get the money
even before doing the job.

32
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:46,206
But I had to do a
carnapping job with them.

33
00:01:47,373 --> 00:01:50,843
[Bhaves] That's how
your sister's old gang worked!

34
00:01:51,343 --> 00:01:54,614
She got in trouble--
I can't do this, Boyet!

35
00:01:54,746 --> 00:01:57,983
Why would you...
Did you join them?!

36
00:02:00,552 --> 00:02:01,620
No, Mom.

37
00:02:01,987 --> 00:02:04,090
I didn't join the Siko Gang.

38
00:02:04,858 --> 00:02:07,927
It was just that one job
to pay for Max's bills.

39
00:02:09,162 --> 00:02:10,497
Uncle Boyet.

40
00:02:12,598 --> 00:02:15,467
Kid, sorry,
I know it was wrong, but...

41
00:02:16,603 --> 00:02:19,838
I feel like such a hypocrite
for always saying that...

42
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:25,311
I'd rather die in debt
than live off stolen money,

43
00:02:26,246 --> 00:02:29,248
but it was your life
on the line.

44
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:32,519
I couldn't live with myself
if something happened to you.

45
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:34,920
But...

46
00:02:36,788 --> 00:02:38,358
on the night of the carnapping,

47
00:02:39,192 --> 00:02:40,659
the gang could tell
my conscience was eating me up,

48
00:02:40,793 --> 00:02:45,198
so they had me be the lookout
along with Tiago.

49
00:02:45,998 --> 00:02:47,834
When it was just me
and Tiago in the car,

50
00:02:49,102 --> 00:02:50,736
I told him
I really couldn't do it.

51
00:02:51,704 --> 00:02:53,939
I was about to leave,
but he stopped me.

52
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:55,942
He told me...

53
00:02:58,144 --> 00:02:59,378
to think about you

54
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:05,350
and the money I got from them
to pay your hospital bills.

55
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,854
But I still left.

56
00:03:09,021 --> 00:03:11,657
Then when I got out of the car,
I heard a gunshot.

57
00:03:12,491 --> 00:03:13,492
I went there

58
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,596
and saw Bok and Ute
running away.

59
00:03:18,097 --> 00:03:21,366
Deib's brother was already
lying on the side of the car.

60
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:26,506
The gang left in a hurry
and I was left alone.

61
00:03:28,174 --> 00:03:29,943
I immediately called
for an ambulance

62
00:03:31,610 --> 00:03:33,712
to help Deib's brother,

63
00:03:35,314 --> 00:03:36,515
then I got scared.

64
00:03:37,917 --> 00:03:40,687
I was afraid of going to prison
and leaving you guys.

65
00:03:42,487 --> 00:03:44,324
So I left after calling
the ambulance.

66
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:50,330
I regret everything
that happened that night, Max.

67
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:52,899
Especially now that...

68
00:03:53,432 --> 00:03:56,235
I know our victim
was Deib's brother.

69
00:03:56,936 --> 00:04:00,639
I used to tell myself
I would never be like my sister,

70
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:03,543
but I still became a criminal.

71
00:04:04,843 --> 00:04:06,312
[Randy]
You're not a criminal, Boyet.

72
00:04:06,712 --> 00:04:08,580
You didn't shoot Dale.

73
00:04:09,115 --> 00:04:10,582
Even so.

74
00:04:11,283 --> 00:04:13,019
Sorry... Sorry...

75
00:04:13,385 --> 00:04:15,020
I hope you can forgive me.

76
00:04:17,689 --> 00:04:19,559
-[Bhaves sighs]
-[phone rings]

77
00:04:23,428 --> 00:04:24,831
[stuttering] Deib is...

78
00:04:25,398 --> 00:04:28,334
Deib is calling...

79
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,970
Max, please don't tell Deib.

80
00:04:31,370 --> 00:04:32,504
Not yet.

81
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,874
I'll make sure first
that it's safe for Boyet

82
00:04:35,007 --> 00:04:37,276
to give his witness testimony
to the police.

83
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:39,711
We need to ensure
Boyet's safety first.

84
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:42,148
Do you understand?

85
00:04:42,581 --> 00:04:45,050
-[phone continues ringing]
-[tense music playing]

86
00:04:51,858 --> 00:04:54,961
["He's Into Her" by BGYO
playing]

87
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:51,951
[song ends]

88
00:05:54,586 --> 00:05:56,355
[melancholic music playing]

89
00:05:56,488 --> 00:05:57,889
[Deib] Max, call me back ASAP.

90
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,959
I have bad news
about Dale's case.

91
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,226
Agila's dead.

92
00:06:03,829 --> 00:06:05,997
And we still don't have
the CCTV footage.

93
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,904
Sh*t! I should have made him
send me the video immediately

94
00:06:13,038 --> 00:06:14,240
when he got it.

95
00:06:18,577 --> 00:06:20,713
Or met up with him.

96
00:06:20,846 --> 00:06:22,382
Then we'd have the evidence
right now

97
00:06:22,514 --> 00:06:24,716
to send Dale's shooter
to prison.

98
00:06:28,788 --> 00:06:30,589
I hate myself so much right now

99
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:33,860
for putting that party
at The Barb first. Argh!

100
00:06:37,829 --> 00:06:40,098
Anyway,
I won't go to school today.

101
00:06:40,899 --> 00:06:43,201
The lawyers want to talk to me
and go over the case again.

102
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,819
Sorry, my first text to you
is bad news.

103
00:07:04,857 --> 00:07:07,192
Good morning, MOO. I love you.

104
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:21,540
[melancholic music continues]

105
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:24,944
[Max] Sorry, Deib.

106
00:07:26,245 --> 00:07:28,648
I couldn't answer your calls
last night.

107
00:07:30,048 --> 00:07:33,052
I stayed up all night thinking
about how to talk to you.

108
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:36,555
I couldn't sleep.

109
00:07:37,523 --> 00:07:40,326
I felt like puking every time
I thought about what happened.

110
00:07:43,028 --> 00:07:43,963
Sorry, Deib.

111
00:07:44,596 --> 00:07:46,098
I just found out last night.

112
00:07:47,132 --> 00:07:49,634
Uncle Boyet admitted
he's one of the carnappers

113
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:51,303
the night your brother
got shot...

114
00:07:58,511 --> 00:07:59,478
[Deib] Let's go!

115
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:01,480
You don't have serious damage.

116
00:08:01,613 --> 00:08:02,982
Please, I'm in a hurry!
How much?

117
00:08:03,682 --> 00:08:06,218
- Seriously? How much?
-[phone rings]

118
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:07,920
What?!

119
00:08:08,053 --> 00:08:09,855
Wait, I'm on my way.
Stay there!

120
00:08:10,622 --> 00:08:12,190
Bro, you have a new visitor.

121
00:08:12,658 --> 00:08:13,625
This is Max.

122
00:08:14,226 --> 00:08:16,696
She's the girl who's been
making me really happy.

123
00:08:17,295 --> 00:08:18,396
Hi, Dale.

124
00:08:18,997 --> 00:08:20,333
[Deib] When we first met,

125
00:08:20,466 --> 00:08:22,000
I was in a hurry, because...

126
00:08:22,468 --> 00:08:23,668
I got a tip

127
00:08:23,802 --> 00:08:25,036
that my big brother's shooter
had been found.

128
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:28,608
But because we got
into that accident...

129
00:08:29,274 --> 00:08:30,175
Sorry.

130
00:08:31,343 --> 00:08:32,611
If I only knew...

131
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,947
Max, you always tell me

132
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:39,384
that what happened with Dale
wasn't my fault.

133
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:42,788
But Mom always hinted that...

134
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:46,392
it was my fault.

135
00:08:47,092 --> 00:08:49,294
[Max] You have
to forgive yourself .

136
00:08:50,229 --> 00:08:51,129
Deib...

137
00:08:52,264 --> 00:08:53,533
It's not your fault.

138
00:08:53,765 --> 00:08:55,735
I promise

139
00:08:56,101 --> 00:09:00,172
I won't hide anything from you.

140
00:09:00,572 --> 00:09:01,740
No lies,

141
00:09:02,642 --> 00:09:03,909
no secrets.

142
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:07,879
[Max] No lies, no secrets.

143
00:09:09,514 --> 00:09:10,783
[sighs]

144
00:09:12,585 --> 00:09:15,254
[melancholic music continues]

145
00:09:21,226 --> 00:09:23,296
[Max] Sorry for not answering
last night, Deib.

146
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:25,798
Slept early.

147
00:09:26,465 --> 00:09:27,866
I'm not feeling well.

148
00:09:28,533 --> 00:09:29,835
I'll be absent today, too.

149
00:09:37,509 --> 00:09:38,811
[phone chimes]

150
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:51,724
[line ringing]

151
00:09:51,856 --> 00:09:54,894
-[phone ringing]
-[gasps]

152
00:09:56,796 --> 00:09:57,929
Hello, Deib?

153
00:09:58,464 --> 00:09:59,298
MOO!

154
00:10:00,231 --> 00:10:01,200
Good morning!

155
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:03,201
Still not feeling well?

156
00:10:03,735 --> 00:10:05,937
I can send you food or drinks...

157
00:10:06,438 --> 00:10:07,405
It's okay.

158
00:10:08,673 --> 00:10:09,942
Don't worry.

159
00:10:11,009 --> 00:10:13,712
Probably just a headache
because of dysmenorrhea.

160
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,749
Just tell me how I can help.

161
00:10:17,316 --> 00:10:19,250
Any cravings,

162
00:10:19,719 --> 00:10:21,153
maybe scented candles,

163
00:10:21,854 --> 00:10:23,221
or extra napkin...

164
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:26,258
Thank you.

165
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:29,894
I'm getting better. Don't worry.

166
00:10:30,028 --> 00:10:31,831
I already took some medicine.

167
00:10:32,331 --> 00:10:33,865
You sure, MOO?

168
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:36,268
Yeah.

169
00:10:36,869 --> 00:10:38,004
Okay.

170
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:40,572
Just text or call me anytime.

171
00:10:41,173 --> 00:10:43,842
I'm just a call or text away.

172
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:46,144
Okay.

173
00:10:46,711 --> 00:10:49,148
Alright, MOO.
You should get some rest.

174
00:10:50,282 --> 00:10:51,716
Catch you later.

175
00:10:51,850 --> 00:10:52,817
Bye!

176
00:10:52,951 --> 00:10:54,086
Deib, wait!

177
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:55,921
Yeah?

178
00:10:57,956 --> 00:10:59,125
I love you!

179
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:02,995
I love you so much.

180
00:11:05,063 --> 00:11:06,831
Don't forget that, okay?

181
00:11:08,701 --> 00:11:09,835
I love you!

182
00:11:12,538 --> 00:11:14,005
I love you so much, MOO.

183
00:11:16,142 --> 00:11:17,009
Bye.

184
00:11:19,778 --> 00:11:20,879
[exhales]

185
00:11:22,847 --> 00:11:24,082
[Randy] How well do you know

186
00:11:24,216 --> 00:11:25,750
the people you carnapped with,
Boyet?

187
00:11:26,451 --> 00:11:30,990
I just met Ute and Bok
that night.

188
00:11:31,756 --> 00:11:33,525
Tiago and I go way back.

189
00:11:33,658 --> 00:11:35,226
He's from Mindoro, too.

190
00:11:36,595 --> 00:11:39,298
[Randy] Does anybody else know
about your carnapping plans?

191
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:42,467
No, it's just us...

192
00:11:43,501 --> 00:11:44,503
and Boss.

193
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:46,871
The CCTV video's gone.

194
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:48,506
Apparently,

195
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:51,476
they make it a point to erase
footage every few months,

196
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:53,511
which makes sense, but...

197
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:57,015
But it's confirmed:
Agila sent someone

198
00:11:57,149 --> 00:12:00,452
to get a copy of the CCTV
footage of Dale's shooting.

199
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:03,188
Deib, think.

200
00:12:03,989 --> 00:12:07,927
What did Agila say to you
about this CCTV footage?

201
00:12:09,195 --> 00:12:10,830
[Agila] There's CCTV

202
00:12:10,962 --> 00:12:14,399
where the suspects parked
the getaway vehicle.

203
00:12:14,866 --> 00:12:16,802
We may be able
to see their faces.

204
00:12:17,035 --> 00:12:18,336
Okay, please update me.

205
00:12:18,703 --> 00:12:22,240
[phone ringing]

206
00:12:26,611 --> 00:12:28,681
-[cheering]
-[phone ringing]

207
00:12:28,813 --> 00:12:30,349
-I'll just take this call.
-Okay.

208
00:12:30,649 --> 00:12:32,150
[Agila] Hello?  Hello, sir!

209
00:12:32,283 --> 00:12:34,886
- Sir, I got the CCTV footage!
- Alright.

210
00:12:35,321 --> 00:12:36,989
Just send it to me.
It's too loud in here.

211
00:12:37,755 --> 00:12:39,158
- I'll watch it later.
- [distant cheering continues]

212
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,558
Okay, bye.

213
00:12:41,192 --> 00:12:43,062
[Deib] The night of the
Interhigh championship,

214
00:12:43,729 --> 00:12:44,730
he called me,

215
00:12:45,029 --> 00:12:45,998
but I had to end the call

216
00:12:46,131 --> 00:12:47,500
because we couldn't hear
each other.

217
00:12:48,234 --> 00:12:50,602
I told him to just send me
the video. Had I known that--

218
00:12:50,735 --> 00:12:53,739
If this Agila was calling you,
then of course, it's important.

219
00:12:54,105 --> 00:12:55,274
You shouldn't have
disregarded that call.

220
00:12:55,407 --> 00:12:56,975
You should have asked
to meet with him right away

221
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:58,409
to get that video.

222
00:12:58,543 --> 00:12:59,577
Daniel,

223
00:13:00,145 --> 00:13:02,914
Deib was busy celebrating
his win that night.

224
00:13:03,048 --> 00:13:04,182
He couldn't have known

225
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:06,784
that Agila would get run over
that night.

226
00:13:07,285 --> 00:13:09,889
And it's a good thing
they didn't meet up.

227
00:13:10,022 --> 00:13:13,259
If they did, your son would've
also been in danger.

228
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:14,927
I'm sorry, Dad.

229
00:13:15,727 --> 00:13:16,595
Baby.

230
00:13:17,562 --> 00:13:20,166
Are there any other witnesses,
Attorney?

231
00:13:20,298 --> 00:13:23,134
Yes, our investigators are
trying to find other witnesses.

232
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:26,004
They talked
to the CCTV technicians...

233
00:13:26,337 --> 00:13:28,640
Can't the CCTV technicians

234
00:13:28,774 --> 00:13:32,043
and Agila's associate testify
about what they saw?

235
00:13:32,344 --> 00:13:34,947
Yes, but the best they can do

236
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:37,448
is describe the faces
of the suspects.

237
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:39,083
The police can sketch them,

238
00:13:39,217 --> 00:13:41,787
but it's not going to be an
exact rendition of their faces.

239
00:13:42,254 --> 00:13:46,491
Our best and most reliable
witness is the CCTV.

240
00:13:47,025 --> 00:13:49,094
[Randy]
If Boyet went to the police

241
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:51,897
or Deib's family as
a witness to the crime,

242
00:13:52,697 --> 00:13:56,067
he needs to be able
to identify who shot Dale.

243
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,770
That's the problem.

244
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,374
I'm not sure whether it was
Ute or Bok who shot Dale.

245
00:14:03,841 --> 00:14:05,043
Randy,

246
00:14:05,778 --> 00:14:08,447
if we went to the police,

247
00:14:08,846 --> 00:14:11,015
would they charge me
with carnapping?

248
00:14:11,149 --> 00:14:13,619
[Randy] The carnapping fell
through,

249
00:14:13,918 --> 00:14:15,486
so they can't charge you
with it.

250
00:14:16,187 --> 00:14:18,323
The only crime that took place

251
00:14:18,456 --> 00:14:20,826
was the serious physical injury
of Dale.

252
00:14:21,559 --> 00:14:25,397
Depending on the fiscal,
it can be attempted homicide...

253
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,201
or murder.

254
00:14:29,768 --> 00:14:31,236
[tense music playing]

255
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:32,370
[Daniel]
It's been several months

256
00:14:32,504 --> 00:14:34,807
since my son Dale
was almost killed.

257
00:14:35,474 --> 00:14:38,344
Here's an idea: why don't we
set up a cash reward

258
00:14:38,476 --> 00:14:41,480
for whoever has information that
can lead us to find this killer?

259
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:43,315
That would speed things up,
wouldn't it, Attorney?

260
00:14:43,448 --> 00:14:45,350
-Yes, it would, but...
-Well?

261
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:48,687
I'm afraid what happened
to Agila was a hit.

262
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:51,256
If the Boss of the syndicate
ordered it,

263
00:14:51,389 --> 00:14:54,826
what's to stop him from doing it
also to our other witnesses

264
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:57,028
even before we can get
any testimony?

265
00:14:59,965 --> 00:15:02,668
Randy, I'm worried
about everyone's safety,

266
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:05,037
including Deib's family.

267
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:09,240
Tiago said
Boss has men everywhere.

268
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:10,643
Even the police.

269
00:15:11,277 --> 00:15:13,345
We can't trust anyone.

270
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:24,756
[door opens]

271
00:15:45,076 --> 00:15:46,177
Dad...

272
00:15:47,011 --> 00:15:48,179
Dad, don't worry,
we'll find the--

273
00:15:48,313 --> 00:15:52,717
That night Agila was supposed
to send you the CCTV video,

274
00:15:53,485 --> 00:15:55,921
didn't you worry when you
didn't hear from him?

275
00:15:56,054 --> 00:15:57,255
I did.

276
00:15:58,356 --> 00:16:01,427
I called him immediately,
but he didn't answer.

277
00:16:02,794 --> 00:16:03,961
Then what did you do?

278
00:16:04,429 --> 00:16:05,563
I called him again.

279
00:16:06,865 --> 00:16:08,267
And again. But I got nothing.

280
00:16:08,399 --> 00:16:10,034
So I gathered all my information

281
00:16:10,168 --> 00:16:12,270
and turned it over
to the attorney.

282
00:16:12,403 --> 00:16:16,207
I even gave the suspect's name:
Christopher Santos.

283
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:18,143
And that was it?

284
00:16:20,645 --> 00:16:23,349
I promised Mom I wouldn't get
involved in the case anymore.

285
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:26,784
Don't kid yourself, Deib.

286
00:16:27,885 --> 00:16:31,322
Whatever you do or don't do,
you're involved in this case.

287
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:35,094
Ever since you were little boys,

288
00:16:36,327 --> 00:16:39,465
your big brother Dale has
always watched out for you

289
00:16:39,731 --> 00:16:40,698
and protected you.

290
00:16:40,832 --> 00:16:44,202
Whenever you got in trouble
and you needed him,

291
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,471
he was always ready to help you.

292
00:16:47,806 --> 00:16:48,706
And...

293
00:16:49,841 --> 00:16:51,844
And that's why he was
with you that night...

294
00:16:52,811 --> 00:16:53,912
the night he got shot.

295
00:17:00,385 --> 00:17:01,452
I'm sorry...

296
00:17:05,223 --> 00:17:06,825
Now it's your turn, Deib.

297
00:17:08,126 --> 00:17:10,128
Now your big brother needs you.

298
00:17:10,561 --> 00:17:11,930
Because of this trauma,

299
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,932
his life is not going
to be the same.

300
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:17,502
You do realize that,
don't you, Deib?

301
00:17:19,738 --> 00:17:20,705
So you--

302
00:17:21,105 --> 00:17:24,108
we must do all we can

303
00:17:24,675 --> 00:17:27,980
to make sure he gets justice
for everything he's lost.

304
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:31,250
Can you understand that, Deib?

305
00:17:34,118 --> 00:17:35,220
Yes, Dad.

306
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:37,388
I understand.

307
00:17:39,525 --> 00:17:41,759
-[Bhaves groans]
-Get some rest, Grams...

308
00:17:43,327 --> 00:17:45,564
Slowly.

309
00:17:46,265 --> 00:17:49,867
Max, I can't stop worrying

310
00:17:50,368 --> 00:17:52,304
about your Uncle Boyet.

311
00:17:53,505 --> 00:17:57,843
I hope Deib's family understands

312
00:17:58,544 --> 00:18:02,548
why your uncle couldn't tell
the truth immediately.

313
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:06,652
[phone chimes]

314
00:18:11,522 --> 00:18:12,758
[Deib] How are you, Max?

315
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:14,759
How do you feel?

316
00:18:17,962 --> 00:18:19,263
Hang on, Grams.

317
00:18:29,307 --> 00:18:35,380
[sad music playing]

318
00:18:57,102 --> 00:18:59,403
[exhales sharply]

319
00:19:17,288 --> 00:19:20,526
[sad music swelling]

320
00:19:50,888 --> 00:19:52,723
Nice! Good shot!

321
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:53,991
Layup!

322
00:19:56,728 --> 00:19:57,628
Come on!

323
00:19:59,498 --> 00:20:01,599
Mhmm! Fun, huh?

324
00:20:02,601 --> 00:20:03,801
Stress relief!

325
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:21,987
Thanks, RJ.

326
00:20:26,090 --> 00:20:26,991
I know...

327
00:20:28,926 --> 00:20:30,429
I know I hurt you

328
00:20:31,696 --> 00:20:33,131
and you still hate me.

329
00:20:37,868 --> 00:20:40,605
All that went away when
I saw you crying last night.

330
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:46,044
No matter how much I tell myself
to stop loving you,

331
00:20:47,112 --> 00:20:48,680
that I don't wanna be friends
with you,

332
00:20:50,949 --> 00:20:52,517
we've gone through
so much together

333
00:20:52,651 --> 00:20:53,884
and I can't just
throw it all away.

334
00:20:56,555 --> 00:20:57,990
You're my friend, Max.

335
00:21:00,959 --> 00:21:01,826
Best friend.

336
00:21:03,628 --> 00:21:05,696
Thanks for still being
my best friend.

337
00:21:12,436 --> 00:21:15,874
[monitor beeping]

338
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:17,108
Thanks.

339
00:21:17,675 --> 00:21:19,678
-I'll take it from here.
-Alright.

340
00:21:31,355 --> 00:21:33,959
[Deib] "Did the Warriors lose?
Why the long face?"

341
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:35,727
[chuckles lightly]

342
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:40,832
It's nothing, bro. Sorry.

343
00:21:42,099 --> 00:21:43,868
Just bumps in the case.

344
00:21:45,936 --> 00:21:48,406
But promise, we'll find
the person who shot you.

345
00:21:48,539 --> 00:21:49,641
Okay?

346
00:22:04,556 --> 00:22:05,891
I'm so sorry, bro.

347
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:10,494
If I didn't get wasted
that night,

348
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,730
you wouldn't be here.

349
00:22:13,932 --> 00:22:16,634
We'd be playing basketball now.
You'd be outside...

350
00:22:17,301 --> 00:22:18,202
happy.

351
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,240
You'd hang with your teammates,

352
00:22:25,143 --> 00:22:26,744
go on road trips with me,

353
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:32,116
or be the boyfriend
of the girl you wanted to court.

354
00:22:34,819 --> 00:22:36,520
I'm sorry I ruined your life.

355
00:22:46,097 --> 00:22:46,964
[Dale sniffles]

356
00:22:55,307 --> 00:22:58,175
[poignant music playing]

357
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,281
Me too, bro.

358
00:23:11,522 --> 00:23:14,558
[poignant music swelling]

359
00:23:21,732 --> 00:23:23,300
I'm happy you're here...

360
00:23:24,635 --> 00:23:29,907
where I can see,
hear, and hug you.

361
00:23:31,209 --> 00:23:33,577
I feel like my "Dear Babu"
emails to you

362
00:23:33,711 --> 00:23:35,614
wouldn't be comforting enough
for this situation.

363
00:23:37,015 --> 00:23:37,915
[sighs]

364
00:23:39,151 --> 00:23:41,086
I owe you a lot, RJ,

365
00:23:42,887 --> 00:23:44,890
especially for opening your home

366
00:23:45,022 --> 00:23:47,592
to Grams and Uncle Boyet
here in Manila.

367
00:23:47,992 --> 00:23:48,926
No, Max.

368
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:52,096
I have much to make up for.

369
00:23:53,664 --> 00:23:55,666
I regret...

370
00:23:56,701 --> 00:23:57,635
not being there when
you were in the hospital

371
00:23:57,769 --> 00:23:58,804
fighting for your life.

372
00:24:00,771 --> 00:24:02,039
I should've been there for you,

373
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:07,878
even just through email,
text, or call.

374
00:24:11,615 --> 00:24:12,917
What if you didn't survive?

375
00:24:14,251 --> 00:24:16,821
I wouldn't have been able
to forgive myself, Max.

376
00:24:18,656 --> 00:24:21,692
[bittersweet music playing]

377
00:24:22,326 --> 00:24:23,228
Sorry.

378
00:24:28,232 --> 00:24:30,701
Sorry for what I said
that night, too.

379
00:24:31,536 --> 00:24:33,171
That Deib
is your first boyfriend?

380
00:24:34,271 --> 00:24:35,173
No.

381
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:37,843
You count!

382
00:24:38,742 --> 00:24:39,845
You were my first love...

383
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:42,747
You're my first boyfriend.

384
00:24:44,615 --> 00:24:46,317
I just meant that

385
00:24:47,219 --> 00:24:49,587
it's my first time

386
00:24:49,721 --> 00:24:51,923
having a boyfriend
I can be with everyday.

387
00:24:53,525 --> 00:24:55,125
Deib and I are always together.

388
00:24:56,795 --> 00:24:59,064
It was different for you and me.

389
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:02,433
We were so far away.

390
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:08,973
I didn't get the full experience
of a relationship.

391
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:16,948
[exhales deeply] Sorry, RJ.

392
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:19,884
I'm really sorry.

393
00:25:26,691 --> 00:25:28,425
RJ, I love Deib...

394
00:25:29,426 --> 00:25:30,394
I know, Max.

395
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:33,131
I'm not asking for anything
in return.

396
00:25:34,332 --> 00:25:36,367
I'm not asking
to get back together.

397
00:25:37,935 --> 00:25:39,770
I just wanna be
your friend again.

398
00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:42,807
I wanna be there for you
when you're having a hard time.

399
00:25:43,741 --> 00:25:45,442
It hurts that you don't
love me anymore,

400
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:49,180
but it would hurt more
if you're not in my life.

401
00:26:01,593 --> 00:26:04,762
You think Deib would understand
this situation with Uncle Boyet?

402
00:26:06,865 --> 00:26:08,199
If he loves you,

403
00:26:09,334 --> 00:26:10,402
he would understand.

404
00:26:22,814 --> 00:26:23,882
[Barb] Alright,

405
00:26:24,015 --> 00:26:25,849
I'll get your bill.
Any additional order?

406
00:26:25,983 --> 00:26:27,152
Coffee, iced coffee!

407
00:26:27,285 --> 00:26:29,153
Somebody's thirsty!
Okay, wait here.

408
00:26:29,287 --> 00:26:30,188
[laughter]

409
00:26:31,122 --> 00:26:33,959
Michiko, got a free sample?

410
00:26:34,625 --> 00:26:35,727
I'll make you a food review!

411
00:26:36,394 --> 00:26:38,663
Lorde, if you want anything,
just buy from Madam Barb.

412
00:26:39,263 --> 00:26:42,601
I have no money. Just treat me!

413
00:26:42,733 --> 00:26:44,501
[Migz] Stop asking for freebies,
Lorde!

414
00:26:44,635 --> 00:26:46,403
Wait, wait!

415
00:26:47,605 --> 00:26:49,140
It's not red velvet anymore!

416
00:26:49,273 --> 00:26:51,409
It means you're not baking
for Master Tob anymore!

417
00:26:51,542 --> 00:26:52,644
[Elle] Well, that's for sure!

418
00:26:52,777 --> 00:26:54,278
[Ysay] Nice!

419
00:26:54,412 --> 00:26:56,213
[friends gushing]

420
00:26:56,347 --> 00:26:57,315
You know,

421
00:26:57,816 --> 00:26:59,416
I'm Tochiko's number one fan,

422
00:26:59,550 --> 00:27:02,820
but it's hard to be a supporter
of a canceled love story.

423
00:27:03,087 --> 00:27:04,990
It's like cupcake without icing.

424
00:27:05,490 --> 00:27:06,357
Not as fun.

425
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:07,959
[Elle] That's true!

426
00:27:08,093 --> 00:27:09,160
[Migz] Ooh! Look at her smile!

427
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:10,428
[Ysay]
Who's making Michiko smile?

428
00:27:10,561 --> 00:27:11,462
So,

429
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:13,198
Michiko,

430
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:17,035
is Master Tob gone
from your heart?

431
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:18,836
Have you moved on?

432
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:19,971
[Naih live-selling
in the background]

433
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:22,539
How do you know
if you've moved on, Lorde?

434
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,275
How do you even move on?

435
00:27:24,409 --> 00:27:25,777
Why are you asking me?

436
00:27:25,910 --> 00:27:28,212
Let's ask Ysay,
the "moving on expert"!

437
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:29,681
-Ysay!
-Yeah?

438
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:31,449
How did you move on from Hunter?

439
00:27:34,118 --> 00:27:35,220
We were never officially
together.

440
00:27:35,353 --> 00:27:36,755
-[Elle] Really?
-[Migz] True!

441
00:27:36,887 --> 00:27:39,490
When Hunter moved
abroad with his dad,

442
00:27:40,290 --> 00:27:43,028
we knew we wouldn't survive LDR.

443
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:46,830
So we ended things
before anything became real.

444
00:27:46,964 --> 00:27:48,400
-That's it?!
-Yeah!

445
00:27:48,532 --> 00:27:49,467
It's that easy?!

446
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:53,238
It's easier to move on...

447
00:27:53,971 --> 00:27:56,407
when there's nothing
to start with.

448
00:27:57,275 --> 00:27:58,410
Ooh.

449
00:27:58,977 --> 00:28:03,013
But I heard the fastest way
to move on is...

450
00:28:04,115 --> 00:28:05,583
find someone new!

451
00:28:05,717 --> 00:28:07,451
-Is that so?
-Really?

452
00:28:07,585 --> 00:28:11,388
Yeah! I learned that from
Khloe's livestreams.

453
00:28:11,522 --> 00:28:12,523
But...

454
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:16,627
no matter what happens,
I won't move on from Khloe.

455
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:17,694
Why?

456
00:28:18,128 --> 00:28:21,766
But don't follow my lead.

457
00:28:22,299 --> 00:28:25,103
Move on so I can have
a new love team to ship

458
00:28:25,403 --> 00:28:27,137
while Khloe and I
aren't together yet.

459
00:28:27,971 --> 00:28:30,008
-[friends chuckling]
-[phone pings]

460
00:28:30,842 --> 00:28:32,477
[Migz]
It's strange what love does.

461
00:28:33,711 --> 00:28:35,779
Hi, sisters!

462
00:28:35,913 --> 00:28:40,218
You can now pick up
your orders here at...

463
00:28:40,351 --> 00:28:41,452
[both] The Barb!

464
00:28:41,586 --> 00:28:44,955
Madam Barb, thank you
for today's free drinks!

465
00:28:45,089 --> 00:28:47,692
Nice work, Naih!
Promote our cafe, okay?

466
00:28:47,826 --> 00:28:49,160
-Hello!
-Yes, work it!

467
00:28:49,294 --> 00:28:50,595
Madam Barb,
I'll continue my live!

468
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:52,564
-Go ahead! Welcome!
-Thank you!

469
00:28:52,696 --> 00:28:55,967
By the way, add to cart now!

470
00:28:56,101 --> 00:28:59,369
We only have limited stocks
for our new products!

471
00:29:02,373 --> 00:29:05,876
"@iloveleefanatic: Can I get
the one with the necktie?"

472
00:29:06,376 --> 00:29:08,913
"@rithchelsecretaria: OMG!!!
Lee is so handsome.

473
00:29:09,047 --> 00:29:10,448
Adding to heart now!"

474
00:29:10,815 --> 00:29:13,151
Hey! Lee is not for sale!

475
00:29:13,284 --> 00:29:17,055
Don't thirst over my boyfriend,
go find your own!

476
00:29:17,622 --> 00:29:19,723
[Naih] Just buy Marchessa
beauty products

477
00:29:19,857 --> 00:29:25,529
so you can also attract
someone handsome like Mine!

478
00:29:29,134 --> 00:29:32,036
OMG! Why are you looking
at each other like that?

479
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:34,506
Are you and Ysay planning
another surprise for me?

480
00:29:35,673 --> 00:29:38,409
Ysay! Come here! I'll introduce
you to my viewers!

481
00:29:38,542 --> 00:29:41,578
-Come on, let's go!
-[Michiko] Go ahead.

482
00:29:42,814 --> 00:29:45,482
Hello, sisters! This is Ysay!

483
00:29:45,616 --> 00:29:50,221
My friennie and Naih-Lee love
team's number one shipper.

484
00:29:50,355 --> 00:29:51,122
Right?

485
00:29:51,256 --> 00:29:54,392
She sang the song
Mine wrote for me.

486
00:29:54,526 --> 00:29:55,559
Right, Mine?

487
00:29:55,692 --> 00:29:57,761
She's always been a true friend.

488
00:29:58,695 --> 00:30:01,231
Ysay, can you tell off these
people thirsting over Lee?

489
00:30:01,365 --> 00:30:03,134
Tell them "Lee belongs to Naih!"

490
00:30:03,734 --> 00:30:07,305
-Go, you can do it! Yeah!
-[chuckles] Okay, okay. Uhm...

491
00:30:08,138 --> 00:30:13,778
-"Lee belongs to Naih!"
-Ey!

492
00:30:13,912 --> 00:30:15,413
Oh my God, yeah!

493
00:30:15,547 --> 00:30:20,018
For the delusional people
out there, wake up!

494
00:30:20,151 --> 00:30:22,686
Alright,
I'll give you a freebie--

495
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:24,154
you can have a crush
on my boyfriend,

496
00:30:24,288 --> 00:30:26,290
but you can't steal him!

497
00:30:26,423 --> 00:30:28,159
#NoSnakes

498
00:30:28,292 --> 00:30:30,627
Oh my God!
Let's continue selling, Mine!

499
00:30:30,761 --> 00:30:34,132
Let's go guys, add to cart now!

500
00:30:34,464 --> 00:30:36,267
Tomorrow,
I will talk to the police

501
00:30:36,401 --> 00:30:38,269
to tell them what Boyet knows

502
00:30:38,635 --> 00:30:41,239
and get him
on witness protection.

503
00:30:41,705 --> 00:30:44,675
When we're assured
of Boyet's protection,

504
00:30:45,143 --> 00:30:46,845
he can give his testimony.

505
00:30:47,144 --> 00:30:49,346
Then you can tell Deib
all about it.

506
00:30:50,414 --> 00:30:53,884
Okay, Uncle Randy.
Thanks for all your help.

507
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:55,452
[Randy] You're welcome.

508
00:30:55,586 --> 00:30:56,788
Grams, I'll go now.

509
00:30:58,021 --> 00:30:59,523
Give Max a ride, son.

510
00:30:59,656 --> 00:31:01,593
No, it's okay, Uncle Randy.
I'm fine, RJ.

511
00:31:01,726 --> 00:31:04,863
Max, let RJ give you a ride.

512
00:31:05,262 --> 00:31:08,766
It'll ease my worries
about your safety.

513
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:11,236
I'll go with you, RJ.

514
00:31:14,806 --> 00:31:15,740
It's fine, Uncle.

515
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:17,575
Grams needs you here.

516
00:31:18,609 --> 00:31:20,678
Then I'll wait with you
for RJ downstairs.

517
00:31:22,579 --> 00:31:23,548
Alright.

518
00:31:23,815 --> 00:31:24,682
I'll go change.

519
00:31:33,124 --> 00:31:35,058
I'm glad you and RJ
are okay now.

520
00:31:45,836 --> 00:31:47,171
Are you mad at me, Max?

521
00:31:48,172 --> 00:31:49,307
Uncle Boyet...

522
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:52,676
